(4, 'An unforseen benefit of the financial crisis?', 'I cane across a headline while scouring the news last week that screamed: Majority of homeowners in UK to be mortgage-free within THREE years Which is a remarkable thing to have happen I thought. In fact &amp;#8211; I actually didnt beleive it. Paid in full: According to the report 50 per cent of those with [...]\nRelated posts:\nNew Zealand Banks and the Economic Crisis.\nThe financial crisis explained\nWhy do banks lose customers. Part 1\n', 'I cane across a headline while scouring the news last week that screamed: Majority of homeowners in UK to be mortgage-free within THREE years Which is a remarkable thing to have happen I thought. In fact &amp;#8211; I actually didnt beleive it. Paid in full: According to the report 50 per cent of those with [...]\nRelated posts:&lt;ol&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2008/12/new-zealand-banks-and-the-economic-crisis/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''New Zealand Banks and the Economic Crisis.''&gt;New Zealand Banks and the Economic Crisis.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2009/12/the-financial-crisis-explained/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''The financial crisis explained''&gt;The financial crisis explained&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/why-do-banks-lose-customers-part-1/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Why do banks lose customers. Part 1''&gt;Why do banks lose customers. Part 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ol&gt;', 'Avalon', '2012-10-06 22:54:48', 'http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/10/an-unforseen-benefit-of-the-financial-crisis/', '2012-10-06 22:54:48', NULL, NULL, '0'),
(5, 'What on earth are Westpac thinking?', 'In fact &amp;#8211; are they thinking? There&amp;#8217;s basically a mortgage war on (which is great for anyone about to come off a fixed rate mortgage &amp;#8211; especially if they have some equity in the property. Banks are falling over themselves to steal customers from other banks. Apparently the group brain cell that would tell them [...]\nRelated posts:\nWhy you shouldn&amp;#8217;t get a mortgage from WestPac\nWhat on Earth is ASB Bank playing at?\nWestpac says I&rsquo;m not a person.\n', 'In fact &amp;#8211; are they thinking? There&amp;#8217;s basically a mortgage war on (which is great for anyone about to come off a fixed rate mortgage &amp;#8211; especially if they have some equity in the property. Banks are falling over themselves to steal customers from other banks. Apparently the group brain cell that would tell them [...]\nRelated posts:&lt;ol&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2010/09/why-you-shouldnt-get-a-mortgage-from-westpac/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Why you shouldn&amp;#8217;t get a mortgage from WestPac''&gt;Why you shouldn&amp;#8217;t get a mortgage from WestPac&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2009/03/what-on-earth-is-asb-bank-playing-at/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''What on Earth is ASB Bank playing at?''&gt;What on Earth is ASB Bank playing at?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2009/05/westpac-says/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Westpac says I&rsquo;m not a person.''&gt;Westpac says I&rsquo;m not a person.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ol&gt;', 'Avalon', '2012-10-06 22:54:48', 'http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/10/what-on-earth-are-westpac-thinking/', '2012-10-06 22:54:48', NULL, NULL, '0'),
(6, 'Why do Banks lose customers. Pt3 &amp;ndash; Meeting the bank Manager.', 'So after my less than impressive email from the Newbie Bank Manager, obviously I fired off a (relatively mild) snottogram asking that he re-review my account, and check his facts. (At about the time I sent that, I also got a short apology of the ANZ bank manager for replying to the wrong person &amp;#8211; [...]\nRelated posts:\nWhy do banks lose customers. Part 1\nWhy do Banks lose customers. Pt 2\nCommonwealth Bank Of Australia lose the plot.\n', 'So after my less than impressive email from the Newbie Bank Manager, obviously I fired off a (relatively mild) snottogram asking that he re-review my account, and check his facts. (At about the time I sent that, I also got a short apology of the ANZ bank manager for replying to the wrong person &amp;#8211; [...]\nRelated posts:&lt;ol&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/why-do-banks-lose-customers-part-1/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Why do banks lose customers. Part 1''&gt;Why do banks lose customers. Part 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/why-do-banks-lose-customers-pt-2/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Why do Banks lose customers. Pt 2''&gt;Why do Banks lose customers. Pt 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2011/02/commonwealth-bank-of-australia-lose-the-plot/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Commonwealth Bank Of Australia lose the plot.''&gt;Commonwealth Bank Of Australia lose the plot.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ol&gt;', 'Avalon', '2012-10-06 22:54:48', 'http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/why-do-banks-lose-customers-pt3-meeting-the-bank-manager/', '2012-10-06 22:54:48', NULL, NULL, '0'),
(7, 'Why do Banks lose customers. Pt 2', 'Now Westpac is a different story. The issue is that the property with their mortgage is in Negative Equity &amp;#8211; ie &amp;#8211; it isn&amp;#8217;t worth as much as it was when we bought it, and the debt on it is bigger than the value. There&amp;#8217;s a whole lot of reasons for this, not least because [...]\nRelated posts:\nWhy do banks lose customers. Part 1\nWhy do Banks lose customers. Pt3 &amp;#8211; Meeting the bank Manager.\nArgghhh &ndash; Banks (again).\n', 'Now Westpac is a different story. The issue is that the property with their mortgage is in Negative Equity &amp;#8211; ie &amp;#8211; it isn&amp;#8217;t worth as much as it was when we bought it, and the debt on it is bigger than the value. There&amp;#8217;s a whole lot of reasons for this, not least because [...]\nRelated posts:&lt;ol&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/why-do-banks-lose-customers-part-1/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Why do banks lose customers. Part 1''&gt;Why do banks lose customers. Part 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/why-do-banks-lose-customers-pt3-meeting-the-bank-manager/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Why do Banks lose customers. Pt3 &amp;#8211; Meeting the bank Manager.''&gt;Why do Banks lose customers. Pt3 &amp;#8211; Meeting the bank Manager.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2009/11/argghhh%e2%80%93banks-again/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Argghhh &ndash; Banks (again).''&gt;Argghhh &ndash; Banks (again).&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ol&gt;', 'Avalon', '2012-10-06 22:54:48', 'http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/why-do-banks-lose-customers-pt-2/', '2012-10-06 22:54:48', NULL, NULL, '0'),
(8, 'Unexpected benefits of NZ residency', 'There are many benefits of NZ residency, compared with only being on a work visa. &nbsp;Most of these revolve around not being kicked out of the country if you lose your job, or the ability to travel to and from NZ as you like. An unexpected benefit brought to our attention in the past few [...]\nRelated posts:\nGet Permanent Residency in New Zealand ASAP.\nWork To Residency (WTR) problems &amp;#8211; be warned!\nSilver Fern Visa &ndash; don&rsquo;t hold your breath.\n', 'There are many benefits of NZ residency, compared with only being on a work visa. &nbsp;Most of these revolve around not being kicked out of the country if you lose your job, or the ability to travel to and from NZ as you like. An unexpected benefit brought to our attention in the past few [...]\nRelated posts:&lt;ol&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2009/07/get-permanent-residency-in-new-zealand-asap/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Get Permanent Residency in New Zealand ASAP.''&gt;Get Permanent Residency in New Zealand ASAP.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2010/01/work-to-residency-wtr-problems-be-warned/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Work To Residency (WTR) problems &amp;#8211; be warned!''&gt;Work To Residency (WTR) problems &amp;#8211; be warned!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2009/11/silver-fern-visa-%e2%80%93-don%e2%80%99t-hold-your-breath/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Silver Fern Visa &ndash; don&rsquo;t hold your breath.''&gt;Silver Fern Visa &ndash; don&rsquo;t hold your breath.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ol&gt;', 'Hubby', '2012-10-06 22:54:49', 'http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/unexpected-benefits-of-nz-residency/', '2012-10-06 22:54:49', NULL, NULL, '0'),
(9, 'New Zealand Shakeout &amp;ndash; Meh.', 'So first off there was in fact no Drop Cover or Holding going on in our apartment. On account of I had a monster Migraine all night, and the last thing I was gonna do was muck around getting under the table. Getting out of bed was a big enough challenge, and I only did [...]\nRelated posts:\nNew Zealand Shakeout 9:26am 26.9.12\n', 'So first off there was in fact no Drop Cover or Holding going on in our apartment. On account of I had a monster Migraine all night, and the last thing I was gonna do was muck around getting under the table. Getting out of bed was a big enough challenge, and I only did [...]\nRelated posts:&lt;ol&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/new-zealand-shakeout-926am-26-9-12/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''New Zealand Shakeout 9:26am 26.9.12''&gt;New Zealand Shakeout 9:26am 26.9.12&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ol&gt;', 'Avalon', '2012-10-06 22:54:49', 'http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/new-zealand-shakeout-meh/', '2012-10-06 22:54:49', NULL, NULL, '0'),
(10, 'Why do banks lose customers. Part 1', 'We bank with three New Zealand Banks: ASB who are our main bank, ANZ and Westpac, with whom we have mortgages on our rental properties only. Well I remember the days when we opened those mortgages with ANZ and Westpac, and had them both practically begging us to move all our other banking to them. [...]\nRelated posts:\nWhy do Banks lose customers. Pt3 &amp;#8211; Meeting the bank Manager.\nWhy do Banks lose customers. Pt 2\nNow even our MP&rsquo;s want to know why the banks are ripping us off.\n', 'We bank with three New Zealand Banks: ASB who are our main bank, ANZ and Westpac, with whom we have mortgages on our rental properties only. Well I remember the days when we opened those mortgages with ANZ and Westpac, and had them both practically begging us to move all our other banking to them. [...]\nRelated posts:&lt;ol&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/why-do-banks-lose-customers-pt3-meeting-the-bank-manager/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Why do Banks lose customers. Pt3 &amp;#8211; Meeting the bank Manager.''&gt;Why do Banks lose customers. Pt3 &amp;#8211; Meeting the bank Manager.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/why-do-banks-lose-customers-pt-2/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Why do Banks lose customers. Pt 2''&gt;Why do Banks lose customers. Pt 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=''http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2009/06/now-even-our-mp%e2%80%99s-want-to-know-why-the-banks-are-ripping-us-off/'' rel=''bookmark'' title=''Now even our MP&rsquo;s want to know why the banks are ripping us off.''&gt;Now even our MP&rsquo;s want to know why the banks are ripping us off.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ol&gt;', 'Avalon', '2012-10-06 22:54:49', 'http://www.avalonsguide.com/anab/2012/09/why-do-banks-lose-customers-part-1/', '2012-10-06 22:54:49', NULL, NULL, '0'),
(11, 'Early morning at the Auckland Domain', '&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Early morning at the Auckland Domain&quot; href=&quot;http://www.aucklanddailyphoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/a06102012-3723-5-1150.jpg&quot; rel=&quot;lightbox&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-full wp-image-8491&quot; title=&quot;Early morning at the Auckland Domain&quot; src=&quot;http://www.aucklanddailyphoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/a06102012-3723-5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Morning in the park&quot; width=&quot;720&quot; height=&quot;375&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\n&lt;/a&gt;Morning in the park, Auckland Domain&lt;br /&gt;\nClick image to enlarge&lt;br /&gt;\n&lt;a href=&quot;http://blackandwhiteweekend.blogspot.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;To enjoy the work of other Black &amp;amp; White enthusiasts, Please visit The Weekend in Black and White!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n', '&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Early morning at the Auckland Domain&quot; href=&quot;http://www.aucklanddailyphoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/a06102012-3723-5-1150.jpg&quot; rel=&quot;lightbox&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-full wp-image-8491&quot; title=&quot;Early morning at the Auckland Domain&quot; src=&quot;http://www.aucklanddailyphoto.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/a06102012-3723-5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Morning in the park&quot; width=&quot;720&quot; height=&quot;375&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\n&lt;/a&gt;Morning in the park, Auckland Domain&lt;br /&gt;\nClick image to enlarge&lt;br /&gt;\n&lt;a href=&quot;http://blackandwhiteweekend.blogspot.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;To enjoy the work of other Black &amp;amp; White enthusiasts, Please visit The Weekend in Black and White!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n', 'Lachezar', '2012-10-06 22:54:50', 'http://www.aucklanddailyphoto.com/2012/10/06/early-morning-at-the-auckland-domain/', '2012-10-06 22:54:50', NULL, NULL, '0'),
